title: Calories in Cane's Chicken Fingers
meta_description: Discover calories in canes chicken fingers, including macros like protein and fat, per tender basis, and serving tweaks for Raising Cane's tenders.
assumptions: Fried, breaded chicken tenders from Raising Cane's, standard size (~45g each), no sauce or sides.
disclaimer: Nutrition varies by location, batch, frying oil, and portion size. Check Raising Cane's app or site for latest values.

quick_answer.text: One Cane's chicken finger provides ~130 kcal and ~14 g protein.

label_note: Values mirror Nutrition Facts labels for easy comparison with restaurant info.

faqs.q: How many calories in one Cane's chicken finger?
What are the macros for Cane's chicken fingers?
faqs.a: Per finger: 14 g protein, 6 g fat, 8 g carbs, 370 mg sodium.

faqs.q: Calories in a 4-finger Cane's combo without sauce?
Are Cane's chicken fingers high in sodium?
faqs.a: Yes, ~370 mg per finger due to breading and seasoning.

faqs.q: How does frying affect calories in Cane's tenders?
faqs.a: Frying adds ~6 g fat per finger; grilling would reduce to ~90 kcal.
